OL,6,FHe added: "We don't recognise the 2.6%
OL,7,Fnumber in Unison's statement and it's
OL,8,Fnot been part of the offer in our
OL,9,Fnegotiations.
OL,11,F"The pay offer is an above-inflation
OL,12,F3.4% increase for 2024/25, with a
OL,13,Fguaranteed pay rise of at least #1,400
OL,14,Ffor those on the lowest job grades,
OL,15,Fmeaning some employees will receive
OL,16,Faround 5.5%."
